                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/5744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 16, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 17—12:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. Referring to the Department’s 157, March 13, 11 p.m. Minister of Finance in
                    principle is in sympathy with the Department’s proposal and will oppose purchase
                    agreement with any other nation. He would like to have negotiations begun as
                    promptly as possible but says that the matter must be taken up with the Foreign
                    Office. This will be done immediately and a further report submitted as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
